Package: iterors
Type: Package
Title: Efficient, Compact Iterators and Tools
Version: 1.0
Maintainer: Peter Meilstrup <peter.meilstrup@gmail.com>
Authors@R: c(person("Peter", "Meilstrup",
                    role=c("cre", "aut", email="peter.meilstrup@gmail.com")),
             person("Folashade", "Daniel", role="aut"),
             person("Revolution", "Analytics", role=c("aut", "cph")),
             person("Steve", "Weston", role="aut"),
             person("John", middle="A.", "Ramey", role="aut"),
             person("Kayla", "Schaefer", role="aut")
             person("Hadley", "Wickham", role="aut"))
Description: A fresh take on iterators in R, offering higher performance and a more compact calling convention. Designed to be backward- and cross-compatible with 'iterators' package, but using the new 'nextOr' method offers significant performance improvements. Ready to go with a big collection of iterator constructors and functions ported from the 'iterators', 'itertools', and 'itertools2' packages.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.6)
Encoding: UTF-8
Suggests:
    combinat,
    testthat(>= 3.0.0),
    foreach,
    iterators (>= 1.0.7)
URL: https://github.com/crowding/iterors
